I think a grounded view of Fantasy magic is fun. Partly this view came about due to the magic system in Unsounded. While the comic itself doesn't overly dwell on how it works, it's clear mages "borrow" aspects from things around them. Things like heat, momentum, pressure, hardness, etc. That's also where the idea of Fantasy flight comes from: A mage in the setting has been trying to create flight and having a very arduous job of it, while just creating a spinny thing that rotates a propeller would be the easiest thing in that setting. Come to think of it, smart construct that do non-smart things are fairly common in the setting as well.
